Empirical Methods
https://bvasiles.github.io/empirical-methods/

This is the Spring 2026 offering of this course. For older versions, see here: Spring 2024 • Fall 2022 • Spring 2021 • Fall 2018.

Empirical methods play a key role in the design and evaluation of tools and technologies, 
and in testing the social and technical theories they embody. No matter what your research area is,
chances are you will be conducting some empirical studies as part of your work.
Are you looking to evaluate a new algorithm? New tool? Analyze (big) data? 
Understand what challenges practitioners face in some domain?

